Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a pale-red pottery vessel, the fabric is grey in section, interior slightly grooved, exterior covered with a burnished cream-coloured slip and with remains of two lines of black-painted hieratic text, smudged in places, identifying contents as year 9 pressed meat.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393150) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393150)
